        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] The Angel, i.e. messenger, of Jehovah is the personification of Jehovah. Observe that in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Genesis 16:10",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " He identifies Himself with Jehovah, expressing in the first person sing. what He will do (cf. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Genesis 21:18",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Genesis 22:15-18",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ").",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "In all probability, in the development of religious thought, the Angel of Jehovah marks an intermediate stage between the simple anthropomorphisms of Genesis 3, 11, 18, and the later, more spiritual and abstract, conception of the Divine Being.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "a fountain of water",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] i.e. a spring of water, which in the desert would mean an oasis towards which tracks would converge. See ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Genesis 24:13",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".",
